Bring a large #pot{} of salted water to a boil.

> TIP: For quicker boiling, boil half the water in an electric kettle, then transfer to pot. Move on to next steps while water comes to a boil.

Add @ramen noodles{4.5%ounce}; cook until just tender, ~{1-2%minutes}. Drain and rinse noodles under cold water. Toss with a drizzle of @oil{1%drizzle}.

Wash and dry produce. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Halve @lime{1}. Roughly chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}.

Rinse @shrimp{10%ounce} under cold water, then pat dry.

Drizzle @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in a very hot #pan{}. Add shrimp, scallion whites, @bok choy and napa cabbage{4%ounce}, @shredded carrots{4%ounce}, and @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until shrimp are cooked through and veggies are softened, ~{4-6%minutes}.

> TIP: While shrimp and veggies cook, move on to next step to mix sauce.

In a #bowl{}, combine @sweet soy glaze{1/2%cup}, @sweet Thai chili sauce{2%ounce}, @ponzu sauce{12%milliliters}, and @honey{2%teaspoon}.

> TIP: Use scissors to open packets quickly!

Transfer sweet soy mixture to pan with shrimp and veggies. Add noodles and scallion greens; toss to coat.

Divide noodle stir-fry between bowls; squeeze lime over top. Garnish with cilantro and @sesame seeds{1%tablespoon}. Serve.

> Shrimp are fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.